caption: Came here twice since I found out about it, only separated by my day off. My new favorite place for lunch around here. Everything is reasonably priced. Nice size portions. The yum num, beef salad with lime, is awesome. Exactly what I expected. Red curry us so good. We'll be returning often. Only bad thing I can say is I ordered the beef with my curry and they gave me chicken, but it was still delicious. Hope y'all support this establishment. You won't regret it.
Good food

I came here on the New Year's Eve and ordered Vada-Pav. It was really really good. This was way better than some of those restaurants in NJ and NY. Customer service was very good. Deepak in the from is super welcoming and friendly. This place is super clean I will come back here again. I recommend this restaurant to everyone.
The madala dosa is DELICIOUS. Definitely a win, great price too. It comes with a zesty sambar. Ten bucks!

I went to get lunch from Spice 6 and noticed the employees making the food in the back did not have on their mask or gloves. With everything going on with COVID you would expect restaurant employees to be practicing the proper precautions and wearing their mask and gloves while preparing food. Not to mention it is now a requirement for everyone to wear mask especially people preparing food.

I’m a regular of this awesome restaurant for a reason! You’d be hard pressed to get such a variety and quantity of food for such a killer price ($10-13). The ingredients are always fresh and quality, and the spices are plenty. Highly recommend this place to anyone!

Ordered a build you own naan pizza with a mango lassi. It was love at first bite. The pizza was full of flavor, and the mango lassi was very very tasty. You could taste how pure the mango was!  I highly recommend trying this place, and trying the mango lassi. Since you build your own bowls, pizzas, wraps, etc, a customer can come with thousands of combinations, I’m sure you can’t go wrong with any combination either!  Enjoy!
Simple selection and good food
Service is great. I love the Naan pizza. Many options, Chipotle style.
Wonderful Indian food. Quick and delicious in Chinatown 🤙

The place was soo clean and i loved the food.. perfect taste and despite of the COVID situation they maintained the hygiene. And in less number of staff Raj was at its best he ran around to serve us and give his best.. must try place.

Really great food. I usually get takeout but they have been closed a lot recently even though it shows that they are open online. This has been an issue when I try to order online for the past 3 months. Hope it reopens soon and makes delivery available again! Meantime, having to find another restaurant for Indian food.

Channa masala is my favorite vegan Indian dish. There are subtle variations between restaurants and I've never met a Channa masala I didn't like. This is my second time to order economy boosting delivery service from Spice 6. I always order the spicy because it's nice-y. There's definitely HEAT but no fire with each bite. The portion size is HUGE! 24 ounces, to be exact. Surely enough for 2 or 3 servings. I forgot that they give you free naan on the side. My mouth, stomach, and wallet are happy and satisfied.

This place is usually great, but they have been closing randomly so often recently. The last 4 times I've tried to order (generally afternoon of weekday or mid-day on the weekend) they're closed without reason. This used to be favorite spot but I'm going to have to move on, need something more consistent.
Delicious Indian. The Chaats are large enough that they could be a meal all on their own.
Overall good food and nice interior. Not exactly authentic, but flavorful and delicious nonetheless.
The food is really flavorful and delicious, there are many options and different price ranges. Good place for a quick lunch.
The dosas are very good and filling. They taste amazing and most are gluten free. Many veggie options.
Restaurant itself is nice but the food leaves a lot to be desired. Naan comes out burnt and the butter chicken is chewy and tastes too salty.
Food good

I'm not usually a fan of corporate/chain establishments, especially copy cats (i.e. Chipotle, or IDOF). That said, the service was quick, the food was delicious, there was lots of it, and it was inexpensive. I guess some business models are nearly fail safe...
I love this place! The chickpeas are so good I’ll go for a bowl of them solo. Fresh ingredients and friendly staff!
Delicious Indian Naan Pizza! Cool approach to fast casual Indian food, always get excellent service here and the food is mouthwatering.
Their button chicken is a little pricey but taste great. Wish they had a lunch butter chicken option.
It's okay
Get the lamb on biriyani! Delicious Indian food for a quick meal, much better alternative to other fast food restaurants.
The food is so flavorful and the menu is way bigger than it appears! Make sure you get a water cup....the spice in the name is there for a reason!

Great fast casual Indian restaurant!! The food is wonderful and the portions are large - you get lots of options on how to customize your dinner. Highly recommend if you are looking for a quick place to ear before a game or concert at the arena.
This is a great counter service restaurant. Great taisting food
Good food and nice and clean ambiance! Its one of the few places in DC that serves Dosa - and does it justice.
The food are seasoned well! I love the food.
Welcoming staff and testy food.
Good Indian food quick.

I feel its over hyped, the taste was okay to me. I liked the concept of naaniza and rice bowl. You wont find authentic indian food. Dosa was good though. I expected more variety and better flavour. Instead of reusing same gravy in all dishes.

We visited this restaurant on our last visit to DC. Definitely became our favorite spot for the time we were there. We took a pit stop again this time but were not impressed at all. Food was below average. We threw away the papdi chat as the papdi was old and stale.

Good food. Seating arrangement and ambience are close to any day food place which goes with the nature of good being served. Staff is friendly and welcoming. I would have given a 5 star if their vada pav was anywhere close to being good. Please get rid off it from the menu. Everything else is really nice and tasty.

The restaurant is right around the corner from the decorative bridge. It is very nice on the inside and the people are friendly and willing to answer questions about the menu. I love that the items are labeled Vegan and Gluten free when they are. It was a great experience and the Idli Sambar was absolutely delicious.  I will be trying more of their menu soon.

Being born and brought up in South India myself, I was raised with dosa twice a week! I loved this place and the food. It tasted exactly like it does back home in India. I was really wishing I could try everything on their menu. The lassi was pretty great too. If you're looking for some good south indian food, this is the place.
Nice fusion and good taste
Fast, inexpensive, delicious and great service! Thank you!
Loved dosa and medu vada....ambience is quite and nice..
Really good food.

Really delicious and fast Indian food! I had a rice bowl with paneer and lots of different toppings. The ingredients were fresh-tasting and yummy, and the portion was large, leaving me with leftovers for the next day. The service was fast and friendly! Lots of places to sit and eat inside.
Pretty reliable Indian fast casual restaurant! Tasty, reasonably-priced food in a clean, modern restaurant. This was my first visit, but I will surely be back to try some of their other dishes :)
Consistent good taste
Cool concept.
Go, Go, Go. Highly recommend this place. Awesome food, quick service, cheap eats, great staff. If you have palate for Indian food, then u wont be disappointed and will thoroughly enjoy the food here.
Really great chicken, not too spicy but well seasoned, seems fresh. Naan bread is very pleasant also.
Super, indian halal food. And the personnel are excellent
Best place for Indian Food
Pretty dang good.  Try the spicy chicken.
Great dosa, absolutely recommend

One my new favorite indian food spot in DC. Good cafe ambience. Great food quality and taste. Mango lassi, dosas and naan pizza are top rated. Good vegetarian options. Reasonable on pricing. The staff is friendly.
Love this place!  I've never ordered rhe same thing twice, and i have never been disappointed!
This spot is amazing and the food is tremendously tasty.
Great...  The pizza nun with spicy chicken, kadhai masala was lip smacking

Spice 6 is my go to restaurant if I'm around Chinatown. Their naan pizzas and dosas are my favorite. Its a great concept, the food is delicious and the service is friendly. I recommend this place to everyone, even if you're not familiar with Indian food.
One of my go to place for quick Indian food around the area. I like their 'onion rava masala dosa' and 'paneer dosa'
Awesome food and friendly staff
Try their naan pizzas they are best in DC don't miss
Consistently amazing. Full of flavor
They change up the menu. Vegetarian options are good. Ive found one pita that i like now.  My favorite was still from last winter. Hope they bring it back.
2.5 stars. Nothing is bad.....just nothing is good either. Delivery was rapid and the food well packaged. I wish they had spent more time making the food taste better.
Wow, could you impress me more with even worse indian food? is that actually possible?
Great atmosphere and great food. The Gulab Jamun could be a lot better however the item selection is great as is the general taste.
Great Indian food. Reasonably priced.
Really excellent food.  Our family had two bowls, one kabob plate, and one naan pizza.  All three things were great and the service was friendly.
Their naan bread pizza was pretty good
My favorite fast food place with modern Indian

The food was delicious. You pick mains, sides, and sauces from a list of options, and the staff was helpful with suggestions. Prices are fair. The only issue we had was cleanliness. Some tables were left uncleaned the whole time we were there and the restroom could use some tidying.

Food was tasty, ordered a pizza, menu was easy for people who have common sense. Just read, these days people need every damn thing given to them and if not they cry Nd gripe. Don’t listen to these “local guides” who are European decent they are used to bland potatoes and broiled beef knuckle. Easy to find same block as Chinatown. Bomb food, of course gentrified prices are expected so no gripes. I’m Guyanese , not Ghanaian, Guyanese so I know spices and seasoning.
Like a chipotle for Indian food. Reasonable priced and sooooo good and customizable. Location is clean and service is good!
Good food!

Very bad unprofessional displeasure welcome I received during my follow ups with my applications I applied for twice  I was greeted in a antisocial manner like I wasn’t welcomed and asked to leave if I wasn’t buying anything when I was charging my phone and staying cool due to the heat condition for anyone need to know they was favoritism over not hiring me and not being in they store
Loved the food. It has all the choices you need to create your ultimate dish and if you're out of ideas, don't worry, they still have great meals that will make you come back for more.
Yummy

Almost a great concept.  The base meal was pretty good Indian food.  The toppings looked more like they belonged in a taco bar. The garlic naan lacked the traditional level of garlic. Lots of potential.

Great experience, and good food. But, they need to make their menu more clear. I am Indian and I had a hard time ordering food that I eat everyday, 'coz the menu was so confusing. But, we ordered three things that was not in their print out menu, but was written on their wall and it was all delicious. We sat outside and people passing by kept talking about how wonderful the food looks and smells, but I wonder how many people actually are able to figure out the menu and order what we ordered.
Excellent food. Great ambience. A must visit restaurant for everyone.
Good south indian street food. Good ambience in the afternoon.
The food was nasty....but the staffs are trying to convince me why the food is so. Isn't funny to convince a 45 yr old Indian guy abt mysore masala dosa:-)
Surprisingly Very good Indian food.

If your traveling DC for weekends, this is not the place to have your food. I ordered chicken Biryani and I got some chicken curry mixed with some flavored rice. Guys please search for better place to have decent food.
American take on Indian food. Ordering is reminiscent of Chipotle which was odd at first, but the food was excellent. Staff was friendly.
Dosas are amazing!
One of the best joints to have Indian food
Great concept. Food was pretty good. Definitely not getting a full authentic taste and style but you don't get that with fast casual concepts.  Would definitely return. Everyone was helpful and nice.

This place is amazing, imagine an Indian version of Chipotle! The flavors are spot on, and it is so much food for what you are paying! A group of 6 of us came across this place and decided to try it, and every single one of us loved it! The owner is also super nice! Please please bring a location to Richmond VA!!
Delicious food, good vibes

Good food... Awesome service...  Vibrant environment... Their naan food is best! The fusion of the Indian food in Indian style is great. Naan pizza is a creative concept, but it's not that great as it lacks cheese which is the main ingredient of pizza. Rice bowl is another Mexican Indian fusion which is also great. Mango lassi is worth to go for after finishing your meal.

A couple of  Indian friends had recommended this place for decent Indian food. The place has a vibrant decor and serves fusion Indian food. So you get rice bowls with a variety of toppings, naan pizza and the like. The concept of Indian bowls seems to have taken off well going by the popularity of the place, though the majority of the patrons were Indian. They took an extraordinary long time to serve the dishes other than the bowls. I wasn't very pleased with the texture of the uttapam and the batter had also gone a little sour. But the samosa was very crisp and made well. Overall I'd say a decent place for Indian food in the downtown DC area.
Love the dosas here!
Good indian food. Ate vada and masala dosa . Both are good taste. Has lots of other varieties of indian dishes.
If you like rice bowls, add this place to your list.
Amazing food...and great service
A good atmosphere. Good food. Not impressed though. No complaints though. Except there was hair in my girls food which was replaced and a guy came in to solicit some money to buy things. 😕
Good location and great dosa!
One of my favorite Indian food places. The food is cheap and authentic. The chutneys are my favorite!
Nice food. Liked the chai and bhel

Stopped in for lunch -- had a naan 'pizza.' Start with a garlic naan, then layer on a curry, spicy chicken, lots of vegetables, cheese and a spicy green chutney.  Bake for a bit. Tasty and a bit spicy, large portions, reasonable prices.
(Translated by Google) Perfect Indian cuisine  (Original) Perffered indian cuisine

This was good food for lunch time. I got the naan roll and mixed chat. Naan was too much compared to protein and also the tofu did not taste that great. Paneer was good but the naan could use more liquid so it's not so dry. Chat was amazing.
Good food, but their online ordering system is unreliable. Expect to wait for your pickup order.

Food was delicious but was slow to come out. My friend ordered a side of naan with his bowl and it came out after he had finished his meal. We had been sitting for 30min before we received our dosa order. I’d come back here but not if I were in a hurry.
Delicious food, friendly staff, and a welcoming interior space. A great place to grab a quick lunch.
I love the food here, the spice is just right. The portions are amazing and the staff is very friendly and accommodating.
Nice and convenient. The staff is friendly and caters authentic vegetarian food.
This place looks so good, Biriyani tastes yummie Highly recommendable 👍🏻
A nice hotel to get Indian food
Best Indian joint I’ve ever visited!!! Had it twice during a 5 day trip.
I already love Indian Cuisine but this street food takes it to another level! Everything is delicious

I came by to get a bowl and actually found it sort of disappointing.  I liked the décor and the idea enough to give it another try, this time I ordered a Paneer wrap.  I actually found this to be a lot more enjoyable meal.  I wonder how my next visit will treat me.  Let's get it.

We were full of expectation when we visited Spice 6. The ambiance is good for a fast casual restaurant (think Chipotle for Indian foods). Being vegetarian is sometimes tough as the choices at restaurants are immediately limited. However, the menu did not disappoint.  We were 3 people so we ordered 3 different dishes and tried it. First up, vegetarian naan pizza. Paneer+onion+bellpepper+jalapeneo+cheese. It was awesome to taste - except for couple things. Salt was a bit on the low side (yes it is subjective) and spices were Americanized (again subjective). Some people may like it, some may not. We landed more towards the like column but wished for more salt/spices.  Next up was Rava Onion Masala Dosa. The dosa itself was good but the Sambhar was extremely spicy (Naan Pizza not that spicy but Sambhar extremely spicy???). Both the chutneys supplied had extra salt. Essentially, the consistency was lacking but the taste was great.  Third dish was Chili Paneer Dosa. This dish, at best, was barely decent. The dosa had very little amount of oil. The chili paneer did not seem crispy (as a lot of chili paneers are) and again, the chutneys were salty and sambhar extremely spicy.  We also ordered Mango Lassi. This seemed more like Mango Milkshake than Mango Lassi. The thickness was off and the taste made it feel like it was *not* made from yogurt.  So the overall question: Would I recommend this restaurant. Yes, I would. I loved the concept. I loved the food. I loved the ambiance. I just did not like the inconsistencies in spice levels. Hope they make the spiciness more consistent.

Great food, pretty ambiance and priced decently. Its a select and choose and customize like chipotle but Indian food. You have biryani rice and plain rice with various veg curries and meat curries. You can mix n match and add any toppings you want on top. You can also have breads along with rice. You have nice Dosas as well and Indian dessert

Very good, easy, quick, and inexpensive. We had a tough time finding decent food and most restaurants had a long wait because we were part of a 28,000 person conference. We were in town 6 nights and ate here three times. Rice bowls and naan wraps were great.
Amazing food. Well seasoned. They make the best naan pizza in town. Staff are welcoming and friendly.
Slow

This would be a five star review if not for the simple fact that the last 3 times I've come, my order was lost in transit. The food is incredible. It is without peer in the area. The organization, however is almost inconceivably ragged. No attempts by staff to rectify the situation or even apologize for the issue. Unfortunately I'll probably still come back here regularly for the food's sake.
A modern Indian fast food restaurant. It’s pretty good. I enjoy the food and the service.

Daughter got the masala dosha (spicy potato) and I got the chicken kabob. Mango lassi has cinnamon, FYI. Daughter loved it, I prefer it straight up. Spicy food isn’t too spicy, Americana spicy. Overall really good food and empty after the caps game. Fans don’t know about this place. The lines at the other places were insane. Friendly staff

Place is completely disorganized and food is mediocre at best. The lamb itself when it finally arrived (24mins later due to multiple screwups and me getting someone else’s kitchen platter) was good enough. Samosas tasted as if reheated in a microwave.
Probably the best Mysore Masala Dosa I have ever had in US!

For the second time this trip D.C. is showing off their fast service game. Imagine a Chipotle that serves Indian food and you have Spice 6. But better local and doesn't charge an arm and a leg for menu modifications. The apps are better then the entrees, but the curry is no slouch. Chinatown continues to amaze.

As far as fast food goes, I really liked this option. It is a nice change if pace from the usual suspects. You choose your base, meat, toppings and sides as you walk along the counter. The staff is friendly and efficient. They also have all sorts of Dosa as well as more traditional foods. The tables are a little crowded inside.

I don't understand how this place got 4.8 rating. I trusted the reviews and ordered food from here. That was the yuckiest chicken biriyani I ever tasted! Who puts corn in a chicken biriyani? Masala was so bad, my kids refused to eat it. And butter chicken went to trash! They should mention in their menu that butter chicken is sweet!! Masala Dosa was okay...that was the only consolation! We will never order from here again.
I get the naan wrap almost every time and I'm never disappointed.
If you're ordering dosas be prepared to wait a long time, really inefficient ordering system for a lunch place.

Nice Indian food Chipotle-styled place where you can get your lunch rice bowl or salad bowl with Indian food ingredients. The interior is nice and new and the food is of good quality and flavor.  Good place for lunch or a quick dinner. The service is exactly like a chipotle-styled resturant where they build your order in successive steps.
Quick and good.  Not a ton of selection, but the food is severed like Chipotle, just Indian food.  Plenty of seats to enjoy.

Are you hungry for Indian food?  Dreaming of spicy masala and creamy paneer but not sure where to go? Is Rasika too expensive and fancy? Same with Bindaas? Think Indigo is a poor value? Have so many places been a salty disappointment? Well, look no further! Spice 6 is what you're looking for. Awesome, tasty food. Lots of southern and northern Indian options. Good portions, reasonable prices (think Chipotle/Chop't prices), so great value! The dosa was crispy and really good. Looking forward to trying other dishes on the Dosa menu.
Great Mexican themed Indian food. Love their food and location.
Amazing authentic affordable Indian food. As someone who grinds his own spices and cooks Indian food all the time, this is the quality type of food you'd get straight from India.

Flavorful, fresh and affordable South Indian food. Great opportunity to experience dishes like Dosa and Chaat without investing a lot of time and expense into a more formal sit down restaurant. This food is really tasty, the employees friendly and helpful in guiding you through exploring this approachable and savory food. Highly recommend.
Amazing place for a quick pick up or dine in during rush lunch hours at work. Never disappoint. Great food and flavor.
The best dosa in USA I can say. Chicken kabab tastes so aunthentic. Oh my god! Am in love with this place. I will recommend every Indian who visits DC

Amazing chilli paneer dosa!!! As a south indian with a lifetime of experience eating dosa, I can vouch for the authenticity and deliciousness of the dosa/sambar/chutney. It was sooooooooo good. Chili paneer was delicious as well. So happy this has come to DC!

Daniel is so professional and friendly and is knowledgeable about the food. Food is good and service is amazing. We make an effort to go more often thanks to the inviting staff like Daniel and Jessica!
Very nice
Nice setup, tasty food, fast service, friendly staff, caring owner. What else could you ask for.  Visited the place with Kids and ordered Dosas and Naan-Pizza. It was amazing. Thank you Spice 6.

I was craving Indian food last week but did not want to stop and sit down at a full-service restaurant. Enter Spice 6.  Spice 6 allows you to make your own bowl with a base, a protein, sauces and toppings. It's a welcome addition to the fast casual dining scene in DC and offers a more unique set of flavors that are sorely lacking here.  I ordered the salad with the spicy chicken and the regular chicken. I got the tandoori sauce and some other kind of sauce.  The portions are large, the price is fair and the service is friendly! I also noticed this place was very clean. Whether that is a result of this place just opening up or not is still TBD, but I am really looking forward to coming back here soon.
Great food and staff! Samosa Chaat was so good!
(Translated by Google) Awesome Bhel Puri and Papdi Chaat ... Good experience overall ...  (Original) Awesome Bhel Puri and Papdi Chaat...Good experience overall...
One of my favorite spots for Indian food! I recommend the chicken tikka masala, amazing!

The dosa are perfectly thin and not oily or burned. They have limited types of dosa and do not serve my favorite- Spring Dosa. However it’s downtown DC and it’s inexpensive, quick, clean and fresh! I’ll take it! The tomato chutney was too spicy for me. The sambar was also a bit spicier than I expected but the coconut chutney was on point. Mango lassi is pre-sweetened so I had to miss out. They do serve kulfi and Punjabi food as well. Now all I need is some chaat and Indo-Chinese and i am set. It’s a good place to try for quick and traditional South Indian food. I gave 4 out of 5 only because the spice level was too much.
It’s my first time to enjoy Indian food!

Actually we went to spice 6 outlet in the Massachusetts Ave NW but their Zomato page hasn't been updated yet .  The branch was located at the back of theatre , there wasn't a rush even though it was a Saturday night but the ambience was great with different ethnicities coming in to have Indian type cusine.  Their menu was very creative and I got to see this type of menu in NY too , its a fusion based with Indian cuisines mixed with Italian, Mexican, American etc.  We tried these for the first time : 1)Naan pizza (5/5):  I absolutely loved it for the effort put in , the naan is soft having a thick crust while we get to choose toppings , I Chose paneer cubes and kadia paneer as the sauce for the base. Toppings are mainstream but the finish was lovely. An Italian-indian fusion was amazing as cheese with kadia sauce tasted amazing. The pizza was filling enough for even 2 people and it was quite evident being a fan favourite for the people.  2)Naan wrap (1/5):  Burrito type , It was one regretfull decision we made as it wasnt the greatest fusion cuisine in the menu. The ingredients for the wrap did not go well with the wrap, naan being thick wasn't the best option for a wrap as it was hard to eat and the stuffings came out regularly. I wouldnt suggest this for a good dinner.  3)Raava dosa (4/5):  We had to order something as we couldnt complete the naan wrap, as desired the dosa was soft and given with chutney and sambar, it was good enough and an amazing choice if you're not interested in the fusion menu.

Excellent North & South Indian Food that's dangerously delicious! I wish it wasn't so close to my office. I love going to the one in Mosaic location, and was very excited that another location opened up in DC that also serves dosas! I waited until my wedding was over to try it out, because I knew I would be hooked!  I've come here 1/2 a dozen times and delightfully my way through the entire menu! I'll dish out my favorites: naan pizza with kadhia sauce, biryani rice bowl, paneer kebab, and rava masala dosa. The food is bursting with flavor in every bite. Even the tofu is delicious! The portion sizes are quite generous and feel stuffed after eating 1/2 of an entree, it's so hard not resist devouring all of it!  Here's the scoop on all of the dishes:  - Garlic Naan: Worth the $1 extra that elevates the flavor - Naan wrap: Tasty but really messy to eat as the sauce drips out of it. I recommend not getting it with a sauce or better yet...get the pizza! - Naan pizza: My favorite dish especially with the kadhai sauce. So tasty that i couldn't stop until I ate all of the slices! - Biryani: Skip the brown and white rice. I'm not a big rice fan, but really enjoyed the bold flavor of the spices in the biryani. - Rice bowl: Great carry-out option that's the least messiest to eat. Get the biryani with paneer and tofu! - Kebab Entree: Great option if you can't decide what, it's a nice sampler! The paneer kebab is really tasty with larger chunks and different marinade sauce than the panner served at the front. I would skip the paneer/veggie combo and just get the paneer. Although the container is sealed tight, I don't think it's the best take-out option and would sit down and eat it. - Sauces: The kadhai sauce is my favorite! The palak sauce is good, the tikki sauce is bit spicy, I wasn't a fan of the korma sauce. - Paneer: Cooked well and marinated in a nice savory sauce - Tofu: Surprisingly very good! I LOVE paneer, but so impressed with the tofu that I sometimes get it. - Veggies: Spicy! - Choola: Chickpeas cooked well with good sauce. Recommend the choola over the veggies. - Mixed chat: Nice appetizer, filling enough to be a light lunch with mini samosa and small aloo potato tikki/patty. - Rava Dosa: Very good, Rava dosa is tough to make right, it's a testament on how good a restaurant can make its dosas. The sambar is quite tasty as well with a nice spicy kick. - Palak Paneer Entree: Made fresh from the back and much thicker than the Palak sauce served at the front - Onion Uttapam: The only dish I wasn't a fan of, too doughy and undercooked, I wish it was thinner and crispier. That's probably the only item on the menu that I wouldn't get again. The Veggie Uttampam at the table next to me looked very good though.  The staff is very friendly and welcoming. Even though lunch time is quite busy, they are polite and take your order with a smile.  Although I'm impressed by the extensive menu, it's a bit hard to read. Rotating screens and more pictures would help! My only complaint about the food is that the sauces are a bit runny and I wish they were thicker.  Overall, I LOVE Spice 6 and come here at least once/week with my coworkers. Great places for groups and picky eaters, definitely a crowd-pleaser with so many choices and customization. Always excited to come back!

I visited this place twice on my visit to DC.  - Food was very good. Mysore masala dosa was good spicy. Rawa masala dosa was so crisp. Naan roll and pizza was delicious - ambience is casual. Clean place and clean bathroom. - Staff was polite and friendly - prices were reasonable  Will come again when I visit DC
It's an amazing experience. One of the best places to eat indian food. Loved their dosas. The rice bowl was amazing as well. I will definitely visit again next time I am in washington.
Love this place. Food is great, place is kept well clean and staff is polite. Perfect for a quick and good Indian meal!
Awesome food! Never had naan pizza and goat meat together before and this was amazing!

I first dined at Spice 6 at their flagship location in Hyattsville years ago. I may be remembering it wrong or my palate has evolved, but I left disappointed in the Spice 6 location in Chinatown. Here's why:  1) Space: It's an odd space. It clearly belonged to another restaurant and they quickly threw some Spice 6 design on it leaving a disconnected design that doesn't scream Spice 6.  2) Food: It's average. I ordered the chicken tikka wrap. It was a healthy portion and fine, but not the best Indian I've had in DC (for that go to Navy Yard to Rasa).  There is something to love at Spice 6- their staff are friendly and helpful!
Are you kidding me!!!
Great food & dosas!
Amazing Indian fast casual that tastes like a way better than you expected for counter service. Super friendly and helpful staff!
Good food. The dosas seem to be very popular. Will order those the next time.

Never tried fast casual for Indian food but I was very happy with the end result. The establishment is clean and the food was delicious. I tried a white rice bowl with spicy chicken and the tikka masala Curry and a few toppings. At this price point I can definitely include this as a quick and easy place to grab dinner.
